  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "QUANTITY SURVEYOR",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Perform simple QS function to analyze cost comparison, prepare budget, evaluate and recommend on the award of Sub-contractors / vendors &amp; implement cost control monitoring;</li>\n  <li>Responsible for measuring quantities and taking off if necessary;</li>\n  <li>Prepare Variation Orders, evaluate, recommend &amp; settlement of sub-contractor / vendors’ payments claims &amp; final accounts,</li>\n  <li>Sourcing and negotiations with reliable and reputable vendors / suppliers;</li>\n  <li>Prepare and Issue Work Orders/ Letter of Award to sub-contractor.</li>\n  <li>Manage daily procurement and contract requirements, maintain, monitor and update the procurement database / costing with budget;</li>\n  <li>Assist Management in all contractual and costing matters</li>\n  <li>Any other ad hoc duties as assigned by the management.</li>\n  <li>Examining and reviewing or assessing construction plans and preparing quantity requirements</li>\n  <li>Liaising and working collaboratively with site managers, clients, contractors and subcontractors</li>\n  <li>Gathering and preparing reports, analyses, contracts, budgets, and other necessary and relevant documents and forwarding them to the appropriate management or personnel</li>\n  <li>Providing advice, recommendations, and suggestions to managers and clients on innovative improvements and new strategies</li>\n  <li>Documenting relevant changes in design and updating budgets when required</li>\n  <li>Strong analytical and critical thinking skills, monitor, and manage every aspect of the cost and production of a particular construction project</li>\n  <li>Excellent negotiating skills required to negotiate costs with vendors and subcontractors and ensure the best deals and minimum budget as much as possible</li>\n  <li>Good organizational skills, able to organize, plan, and strategize when necessary</li>\n  <li>Well-developed verbal and written communication skills which will enable to write detailed and concise reports and communicate with clients, subcontractors, and other relevant stakeholders efficiently and effectively</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree Holders in Quantity Surveying</li>\n  <li>Willing to learn and work under pressure</li>\n  <li>konwledge in Mandrain languages to handle queries and feedbacks to associates, clients and customers</li>\n  <li>Minimum 2-3 years of related working experience, with QS experience is a must.</li>\n  <li>Meticulous and good interpersonal skill;</li>\n  <li>Able to work independently under minimum supervision</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
